  "prompt": "What are the top 10 most read articles on Wikipedia?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, Wikipedia doesn't maintain a static list of the \"top 10 most read articles\" because page views fluctuate regularly based on current events, trends, and user interests. However, certain articles consistently rank highly in terms of readership. Here's a general overview of the types of articles that often appear among the most viewed on Wikipedia:\n\n1. **Main Page**: The Wikipedia Main Page itself typically receives the highest number of views as it serves as the portal to the entire site.\n\n2. **Current Events**: Articles related to ongoing news stories, significant events, or trending topics often see spikes in viewership.\n\n3. **Popular Figures**: Biographies of celebrities, politicians, athletes, and other public figures (e.g., **Barack Obama**, **Elon Musk**, **Taylor Swift**) frequently attract a large number of readers.\n\n4. **COVID-19**: The COVID-19 pandemic has led to sustained interest in related articles, including **COVID-19 pandemic**, **Coronavirus**, and **Vaccination**.\n\n5. **Historical Events**: Major historical events such as **World War II**, **9/11 attacks**, and **Fall of the Berlin Wall** continue to be highly referenced.\n\n6. **Technology and Companies**: Articles about widely used technologies and major companies (e.g., **Apple Inc.**, **Microsoft**, **Bitcoin**) are consistently popular.\n\n7. **Entertainment**: Pages related to blockbuster movies, TV shows, and video games (e.g., **Marvel Cinematic Universe**, **Game of Thrones**, **Fortnite**) often see high traffic.\n\n8. **Health and Medicine**: Topics like **Mental Health**, **Diabetes**, and **Nutrition** are frequently accessed by readers seeking information.\n\n9. **Geographical Locations**: Articles about prominent cities, countries, and landmarks (e.g., **New York City**, **Paris**, **Great Wall of China**) are commonly viewed.\n\n10. **Science and Nature**: Pages on scientific topics and natural phenomena (e.g., **Climate Change**, **Black Hole**, **DNA**) attract interest from a wide audience.\n\n### How to Find Current Top Viewed Articles\n\nIf you're interested in the most up-to-date statistics on Wikipedia's most viewed articles, you can use the following resources:\n\n- **[Wikipedia Pageviews Analysis](https://pageviews.toolforge.org/)**: This tool allows you to analyze and explore pageview data for Wikipedia articles over various time periods.\n\n- **[Wikimedia Stats](https://stats.wikimedia.org/)**: Provides comprehensive statistics about all Wikimedia projects, including pageviews for individual articles.\n\n- **[List of Most Viewed Articles on Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Top_25_Report)**: Wikipedia occasionally publishes lists of the most viewed articles, although these lists may vary in frequency and scope.\n\nPlease note that the rankings can change daily based on global events, viral trends, and shifts in public interest.",
